text: Hannah Moore (born August 22, 1996) is an American swimmer, specialising in open water events. She competed in the women's 5 km event at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships, winning the bronze medal. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:American female swimmers Category:World Aquatics Championships medalists in open water swimming Category:Universiade medalists in swimming Category:Universiade bronze medalists for the United States Category:Swimmers at the 2014 Summer Youth Olympics Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Youth Olympic gold medalists for the United States Category:Female long-distance swimmers Category:Medalists at the 2017 Summer Universiade
